HEADWORD: Phanar
<hw>Phan"ar</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧n"⟦dot⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Turk.
<ets>fanar</ets>, fr. NGr. <grk>fana`ri</grk> lighthouse, Gr.
<grk>fana`rion</grk> lantern; -- from a lighthouse on a point projecting
into the Golden Horn.]</ety> <def>A quarter of Constantinople which,
after the Turkish conquest of the city, became the chief Greek quarter;
hence, the Greek officials of Turkey, or phanariots, as a
class.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

